<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 14 at 7:44PM CDT  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...Areas of fog to affect South Padre Island...
Surface observations, web cameras and satellite imagery indicate
that patchy fog is developing over the Laguna Madre and adjacent
near shore Gulf waters. Conditions are conducive for the fog to
thicken and become more widespread over the next several hours
possibly lowering visibility along Padre Island especially near
South Padre Island areas near 1 mile or less. Once the fog sets in
it may remain across the island overnight and a dense fog
advisory may be necessary.
Motorists, are urged to reduce speed, use low beam headlights,
and avoid following other vehicles too closely in areas of fog.</description>
